get.description:
Retrieves all nodes as flat list, roots or nodes's first level children (<b>unexpanded</b>).

<p>/rest/mp/asset-attributes/{id}/nodes</p>

Examples:
<p>/rest/mp/asset-attributes/{id}/nodes?filter=roots</p>
<p>/rest/mp/asset-attributes/{id}/nodes?parentId=22</p>

Note: Using both parameters simultaneously will return an empty array.

<pre>
    [
      {
        "id": 0,
        "label": {
          "en-US": "LBL-000000000"
        },
        "hasChildren": true
      },
      {
        "id": 9,
        "label": {
          "en-US": "LBL-000000009"
        },
        "hasChildren": true
      },
      {
        "id": 18,
        "parentId": 9,
        "label": {
          "en-US": "LBL-000000018"
        },
        "hasChildren": false
      }
    ]
  </pre>

__Security Roles Allowed:__ AUTHENTICATED

patch.description:
Updates attribute's trees.

<p>/rest/mp/asset-attributes/{id}/nodes</p>

Note: nodes with 'children': null are treated as not loaded (lazy GET). If you want to show that
this node has children no longer (both lazy and expanded), then you have to provide an empty array (i.e. 'children': [])

<pre>
    [
      {
        "id": 0,
        "label": {
          "en-US": "LBL-000000000"
        },
        "children": [
