get.description:
Returns all relation definitions.
If there are no definitions, an object with empty collection is returned.
If the user is not logged in, then 401 Unauthorized is returned.
If the client does not provide <code>offset</code> and <code>limit</code> values, then the first 10 relations will be returned.

<p>
The following request will return maximum of 5 relations, after the first 10 from the result set.
<p>GET /rest/mp/v1.2/assets/config/relations?offset=10&amp;limit=5</p>

<br> Response example:
<pre>
 {
     "relations": [
          {
              "name": "My Relation 1"
          },
          {
              "name": "My Relation 2"
          }
     ]
 }
 </pre>

__Security Roles Allowed:__ PIMEDIA_DATABASE_MODULE_ACCESS

Returns all relations for particular asset.
If the request succeed, then status 200 OK is returned and an object with a collection of the relations.
If the request is invalid, then 400 Bad Request is returned.
If the user is not logged in, then 401 Unauthorized is returned.
If the asset doesn't exist, then status 404 Not Found is returned.

<b>GET /rest/mp/v1.2/assets/32532/relations</b>

<b>Example Response:</b>
<pre>
     {
         "relations": [
              {
                  "id": 1,
                  "relationId": 1,
                  "relatedAssetId": 123
              },
              {
                  "id": 2,
                  "relationId": 1,
                  "relatedAssetId": 456
              },
              {
                  "id": 3,
                  "relationId": 2,
                  "relatedAssetId": 456
              }
         ]
     }
 </pre>

__Security Roles Allowed:__ PIMEDIA_DATABASE_MODULE_ACCESS

