put.description:
Update the provided list of publishing channels. Missing or null value fields will be nullified.

request example:
<pre>/rest/mp/v1.2/publishing-channels</pre>

example of a request body:
<pre>
         {
             "updates":[
                {
                 "id": "Publishing_channel",
                 "name": "name",
                 "description": "description "
                },
                {
                 "id": "Publishing_channel2",
                 "name": "name",
                 "renderingSchemeId": 27
                }
             ]
         }
 </pre>

example of response body:
<pre>
     {
         "publishingChannels": [
             {
                 "id": "Publishing_channel",
                 "name": "name ",
                 "description": "description"
             },
             {
                 "id": "Publishing_channel2",
                 "name": "name ",
                 "renderingSchemeId": 27
             }
         ]
     }
     </pre>

validation:
id must be between 1 and 25 characters length. Allowed characters are a-z, A-Z, 0-9, _ and -,
no id duplication allowed(value is case-insensitive),
system channel names are not updatable,
renderingSchemeId is optional and if provided must be a valid download schema id

__Security Roles Allowed:__ PIMEDIA_ORGANISATION_MANAGE_WEB_PUBLISHING

